===Noun===
{{en-noun|~}}

# The characteristics of a society, city etc. which has many different [[ethnic]] or [[national]] cultures mingling freely; political or social policies which support or encourage such [[coexistence]]. {{defdate|from 20th c.}}
#* {{quote-journal|lang=en|date=8 April 1991|author=Barbara Ehrenreich|magazine=Time|passage=Something had to replace the threat of communism, and at last a workable substitute is at hand. "'''Multiculturalism'''," as the new menace is known, has been denounced in the media recently as the new McCarthyism, the new fundamentalism, even the new totalitarianism -- take your choice.|title=Essay: Teach Diversity -- with a Smile}}
#* {{quote-journal|lang=en|date=3 August 2005|author=David Davis MP|work=Daily Telegraph|passage=Britain has pursued a policy of '''multiculturalism''' - allowing people of different cultures to settle without expecting them to integrate into society.}}
#* {{quote-journal|lang=en|date=7 April 2011|title=On a mat and a prayer|magazine=The Economist|passage=Earlier this year he said '''multiculturalism''' had “failed”, that immigrants needed to “melt” into French society, and that “we do not want ostentatious prayers in the street in France.”}}

